  "parent": "sla",
  "notes": "Old Church Slavonic (also called Old Bulgarian), the first literary Slavic language, codified by Sts Cyril & Methodius (9th c.). South Slavic base with nasal vowels /ẽ õ/, yers /ĭ ŭ/, yat /æː/. ⟨щ⟩ has South Slavic value [ʃt] (vs East Slavic [ɕː]). Graphemes follow early Cyrillic; Glagolitic equivalents omitted.",
